    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_F7E78030-1C8C-0135-DC9A-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can add a rubric to an assignment to help students understand expectations for the assignment and how you intend to score their submissions. Occasionally, rubrics are added to assignments when you have an outcome inside of the rubric that you would like to use for alignment purposes. In addition to assignments, rubrics can also be added to <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-add-a-rubric-to-a-graded-discussion/ta-p/1062" target="_blank">graded discussions</a> and <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-add-a-rubric-to-a-quiz/ta-p/1009" target="_blank">quizzes</a>.</p>
<p>Rubrics can be added by finding an existing rubric in one of your courses, or by creating a new rubric.</p>
<p><strong>Note:Â </strong>When you add a rubric to a moderated assignment, any associated outcome results display in the Learning Mastery Gradebook only after final grades are posted.</p>
  </div>
</div>

